## **Complete Web3 Study List for Certifications**

### **1️⃣ Blockchains / Platforms (Foundational Tech)**

* **Ethereum** – Smart contracts, DeFi, NFTs
* **Solana** – Fast & low-cost blockchain
* **Polygon (Matic)** – Ethereum scaling solution
* **Avalanche** – High throughput, smart contracts
* **Cardano** – Proof-of-stake, decentralized apps
* **Binance Smart Chain (BSC)** – DeFi & token projects
* **Polkadot** – Interoperability between blockchains
* **Tezos** – Smart contracts & formal verification
* **Near Protocol** – Developer-friendly, low-cost apps

---

### **2️⃣ Web3 Core Concepts**

* **Smart Contracts** – Self-executing blockchain programs
* **Decentralized Finance (DeFi)** – Lending, borrowing, DEXs
* **Decentralized Autonomous Organizations (DAOs)** – Community governance
* **Non-Fungible Tokens (NFTs)** – Unique digital assets
* **Web3 Wallets** – Metamask, Phantom, Trust Wallet
* **Tokens & Tokenomics** – ERC-20, ERC-721, ERC-1155 standards
* **Oracles** – Chainlink, Band Protocol (connect real-world data)
* **Decentralized Storage** – IPFS, Filecoin, Arweave
* **Layer 2 Solutions** – Polygon, Optimism, Arbitrum
* **Cross-chain & Interoperability** – Polkadot, Cosmos

---

### **3️⃣ Web3 Development Tools**

* **Solidity** – Smart contract programming (Ethereum)
* **Rust** – Smart contracts (Solana)
* **Hardhat / Truffle** – Ethereum development frameworks
* **Alchemy / Infura** – Blockchain node APIs
* **Web3.js / Ethers.js** – JavaScript libraries to interact with blockchain
* **Moralis** – Backend for Web3 apps
* **OpenZeppelin** – Secure smart contract library

---

### **4️⃣ Popular Web3 Projects / Platforms**

* **NFT Marketplaces:** OpenSea, Rarible, LooksRare
* **DeFi Platforms:** Uniswap, Aave, Compound, Curve
* **Gaming & Metaverse:** Decentraland, Sandbox, Axie Infinity
* **Oracles & Data:** Chainlink, Band Protocol
* **Layer-2 / Scaling:** Polygon, Optimism, Arbitrum
* **Infrastructure:** Alchemy, Infura, QuickNode

---

### **5️⃣ Certification-Oriented Skills**

* **Blockchain Basics:** Consensus, mining, staking, cryptography
* **Smart Contract Development:** Solidity, testing, deployment
* **DeFi Operations:** Swaps, liquidity pools, yield farming
* **NFT Creation & Marketplace Deployment**
* **DAO Governance & Token Economics**
* **Web3 Security:** Common vulnerabilities, audits
* **Web3 Wallet Integration:** Connecting frontend to blockchain

